Chilean Stocks: Besalco, Cencosud, CGE, Lan Airlines Advance

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-08-12T21:11:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/chilean-stocks-besalco-cia-general-de-electricidad-and-lan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:24 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index gained 0.9 percent to 4,250.69. The
benchmark index rose 4.5 percent rise this week, its biggest
weekly gain in almost five months.  Besalco SA (BESALCO)  , a Chilean engineering and
construction group, jumped 6.3 percent to 760 pesos, its fourth
day of gains. Construction in  Chile  grew 9.1 percent in June
from a year earlier, the biggest increase since 2008, according
to a  statement  posted on the website of the Chilean Construction
Chamber.  Cencosud SA (CENCOSUD CC) rose 1.1 percent to 2,904 pesos.
 Latin America ’s third-largest retailer by sales signed an
agreement with Brazilian lender Banco Bradesco SA to operate
branded credit cards for Cencosud’s supermarkets in Latin
America’s largest economy.  Cia. General de Electricidad SA (CGE CC) surged 8 percent
to 2,553.4 pesos, its biggest gain since October 2008. The Marin
and Almeria groups will end an agreement through which they
controlled the Chilean energy holding company, according to a
filing sent yesterday to regulators. The agreement signals an
end to fighting between members of the shareholder pact, Jorge Donoso, an analyst at Santiago-based brokerage firm Larrain Vial
SA, said today in a phone interview.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   gained 2.7 percent to 11,708
pesos, its fourth day of gains. Latin America’s largest airline
by market share was recommended for “approval without
restrictions” for its planned takeover of Tam SA by  Brazil ’s
 Finance Ministry .  To contact the reporter on this story:
